Title:
LoadReload

Type:
GitHub Tool

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
LoadReload is a Windows shellcode loader created for a master’s thesis, intended to run Sliver-generated shellcode (notably large payloads). It focuses on evasion and operational stability by decrypting an embedded/loaded payload (multibyte XOR) and resolving APIs dynamically via hashing to reduce static indicators. The project includes anti-emulation timing tricks (BusySleep using KUSER_SHARED_DATA) and a RW→RX memory permission loop aimed at “deconditioning” EDR/memory scanners by wasting scanning resources. It also preloads network-related DLLs to avoid behavioral detections tied to late/odd module loads and supports “module overloading” using an operator-chosen decoy DLL (e.g., edgehtml.dll). Shellcode execution is performed via LdrCallEnclave, an uncommon execution path compared to typical CreateThread/QueueUserAPC patterns. Useful primarily for red teamers, malware researchers, and defenders studying modern loader tradecraft and detection opportunities around memory protection churn, module load patterns, and unusual execution APIs.

Technical Focus:
- Shellcode loading/execution on Windows (LdrCallEnclave)
- API hashing and dynamic API resolution (IAT obfuscation)
- Payload encryption/decryption (multibyte XOR)
- Anti-emulation / timing checks (KUSER_SHARED_DATA-based sleep)
- Memory protection manipulation (RW→RX loops)
- DLL/module load strategy (preloading, decoy module overloading)

Use Cases:
- Researching and benchmarking EDR behavioral detections against custom loaders
- Building/understanding Sliver shellcode execution chains in Windows userland
- Developing detections for suspicious memory-protection churn and atypical execution APIs
- Studying anti-emulation timing techniques leveraging shared user/kernel data
- Testing module-load heuristics (network DLL preloading, decoy/stomp/overload patterns)

Keywords:
LoadReload, shellcode loader, Sliver, Windows, C++, multibyte XOR, API hashing, dynamic API resolution, IAT obfuscation, KUSER_SHARED_DATA, anti-emulation, BusySleep, RW-RX loop, VirtualProtect, memory scanners, EDR evasion, DLL preloading, edgehtml.dll, module overloading, LdrCallEnclave